article.headline: N. Arizona 68, UC Riverside 56
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- DeAngelo Jones and Cameron Jones each scored 17 points and Northern Arizona beat UC Riverside 68-56 Sunday. The victory was the first in four games for the Lumberjacks (3-5), who ended the Highlanders' five-game winning streak. Rudy Meo led the Riverside (5-3) with 16 points and Sean Cunningham added 14. Northern Arizona took a 36-22 lead into halftime after Riverside shot just 6 of 20 in the first 20 minutes. The Lumberjacks trailed 6-5 early, but Cameron Jones scored five straight points and NAU led the rest of the way. Later in the half, the Lumberjacks broke open the game with a 16-5 run. Cameron Jones and DeAngelo Jones accounted for 14 of the 16 points.
